  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the<strong> chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 30-35 min or until golden and crispy – these are your <strong>black pepper chips</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1619786262348-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1619786262348-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1619786262348-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1619786262348-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1619786262348-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a pot over a low heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 20 min, stirring frequently, or until halved in size and golden</p><p>Tip: Cook the onion over a really low heat so it doesn’t burn!</p><p>Once golden, add 3/4 of your <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong> (save the rest for later!) and cook for 3-4 min further or until dark and soft – this is your <strong>Henderson's caramelised onion</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1619786303360-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1619786303360-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1619786303360-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1619786303360-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1619786303360-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is caramelising, combine the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>Henderson's Relish </strong>and your <strong>mayo</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>Henderson's mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1619786347287-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1619786347287-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
